This paper discusses the ability of recurrent neural networks to capture and exploit hierarchical information in natural language processing tasks, which is a common topic in the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The paper also compares recurrent and non-recurrent neural networks in their ability to model structured data, which is relevant to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper may be relevant to Computer Vision (cs.CV) as hierarchical structures are often present in visual data.
